          <div class="histories-texts">
            <h3>
                The History
            </h3>
            <h1>
                The Music is in the Heart of Jakarta
            </h1>
            <p>Jakarta Music Hall is located in Kemayoran, a district within Central Jakarta, it is both strategically placed and designed by JM Architeture Firm in 2009. With the distinctive fusion of sharp architectural insight and strong artistic value, this fine concert hall is able to reach its level of superb acoustics.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="histories-mid">
            
          <div class="histories-texts">
            <h3>
                The Hall
            </h3>
            <h1>
                World-class Concert Acoustics
            </h1>
            <p>Jakarta Music Hall features a stage made of pine wood strategically placed in the center of the six-story hall, audiences at every seat can enjoy an unobstructed and clear view of the performance. Each feature was planned to enhance the warmth and richness of sound in the space, providing a superb aural experience.</p>
          </div>
          
          <img src="../assets/home-2.jpg" alt="">
          
        </div>

        <div class="histories">
            <img src="../assets/home-3.jpg" alt="">
          <div class="histories-texts">
            <h3>
                The Icon
            </h3>
            <h1>
                Special Music Instruments
            </h1>
            <p>Jakarta Music Hall is further complemented by its impressive lineup of special musical instruments. The real highlight of Jakarta Music Hall is its pipe organ which features 3,217 pipes, 57 ranks, and 3 manuals. Built in 1962 by Casavant Fr√®res, this Canada-original organ weighs around a staggering 20,000 pounds.</p>
